If you‚Äôre in Aveiro, this restaurant is an absolute must-visit‚Äîwhether you‚Äôre a vegetarian or a carnivore. It‚Äôs a culinary experience that beautifully blends tradition, innovation, and heart. I can‚Äôt wait to return!

review_text: A place to park near a spectacular beach and town. The area itself is quite basic. You have to pay to collect water, but not to empty either gray or black sewage. There's a parking lot next door where you can also spend the night, but you can't expand your space with tables, chairs, and the like. So, for 5 euros, we preferred to set up the whole Nativity scene and be safe from fines (signs already warn against overnight parking, although you'll later see they don't strictly enforce this). The location of the area is unbeatable. Spectacular beach. There are free cold showers and restrooms at a beach bar opposite the RV area, which you can use.

Absolutely beautiful seafood restaraunt right off the water of Aviero / Costa Nova.

The owner seated us and was very friendly. They helped us pick out some nice wines to pair with the meal and we got some of the best seafood I‚Äôve had in my life. The octopus was cooked perfectly and not the least bit rubbery, it was almost soft and pillowy in your mouth. The prawn was gushing with flavors and was so fresh. The clams had the simplest sauce to simply intensify the natural amazing flavor. And of course, we tried all of the deserts, and they were all to die for. Also, I believe the Sous Chef served our food and was able to answer some questions we had about the meal.

This was one of those truly rare 11/10 dining experiences. The service, ambiance, and food were all literally perfect. Can‚Äôt recommend this place enough!

Me and my partner are vegetarian and were passing by this restaurant saw that they have one vegetarian option so decided to eat there but when the vegetarian plate arrived it was very little portion for what they we have paid. Meal was fried rice with little lentils (18‚Ç¨) it‚Äôs too much to pay for what we eat. I think the can improve the vegetarian meal.
Service and atmosphere were great! The fish was nicely cooked, but i think the sea soup lacked a bit in the seasoning part... It was too mild for my liking and not as rich as i expected!

Great food, an amazing service and the environment was just right.

The appetizers were super, and although the wait for the ‚Äúmassada de garoupa‚Äù was bit more then I anticipated it was well worth the time.

The ‚Äúmedalh√µes de novinho‚Äù was heavenly.

The deserts‚Ä¶. They are must, especially the cookie cake with soft eggs, my goodness just amazing

The service was impeccable. Theatrical yet genuine. If that makes sense. I would say hands down the best service IN the Aveiro area. Everyone that came to our table from greeting, ordering, food presentation, & delivery all had such great service it felt like they had some kind of special training. The fish was fresh and grilled almost to perfection (i prefer a slightly more charred & chewy texture for my red snapper). However, my husband agreed the texture of the fish was quite consistent throughout the entire body of the fish. O and the cookie cake is fabulously naughty!
Great experience. Ate way too much, but the cakes were too delicious not to. Fun experience in an authentic, inexpensive pastry shop. Highly recommend the chocolate cherry cake.

Absolutely disgusting experience! We went in for lunch, thinking a place full of locals must be good. Big mistake.

First, my husband needed the restroom, but a rude, power-tripping cleaning lady blocked both the men‚Äôs and women‚Äôs toilets, making us wait 15 unbearable minutes for no reason.

Then came the food‚Äîawful soup, mediocre pastries, nothing special. But the worst part? The change they gave us. Look at the photo. Moldy, torn, unusable bills! NO ONE accepts them. When I asked for proper money, the cashier just shrugged and refused.

This place has zero respect for customers‚Äîespecially tourists. If you value your time, money, and dignity, stay far away!

Bad and slow service, staff seeming extremely lazy. We waited for 40 minutes until we got fed up and asked where our food was and just then we got served by a different waiter, and we didn't even get what we ordered. The original waiter we had was a guy named Gonzalo, probably the entitled son of the boss.

The ladies inside running the bakery are sweet, through.

Really impressed with my chicken burger .. 4 stars only because I'd have preferred a crunchy roll rather than a soft one, but that's personal preference. The fries were crispy, fresh and tasty.. Great service.. very fast and friendly.

I'm sorry that nowadays the service is not able to apologize.
After asking what is the soup of a day i received the answer that it is vegetable soup. I ordered it.

Immediately after it was placed on the table I smelled meat. Afer asking if it comes with meat the answer was, yes it does, with sausage. I said that unfortunately I don't eat meat and I won't eat the soup.

Of course I had to pay for it in the end without any apology. I understand that I should have checked before ordering whether the vegetable soup by any chance contains meat ... I don't understand that the situation was not resolved in any way and that I didn't even deserve an apology for not being offered any other option or any: "we are sorry for uncomplete information" "we are sorry that we didnt try to understand client's side"....whatever would be accepted and would made one feel kinda let's say heard or seen.

For me a no go

In the radius from 10 meters you already have several shops and restaurants.  Bakery around the corner, fish market, etc. Beautiful beach is a 10-minute walk away.  beautiful hiking trails. Local accommodation apartments with a wonderful location. They have the lake in front and the ocean behind them.
Nearby are the market, excellent restaurants, a bakery, a pedestrian promenade, parks, parking, and shops... everything you need for a pleasant stay.
The apartments are fully equipped, have large terraces with great views, and the staff is very friendly.
The apartment is very nice, spacious, and you can cook. There are shops nearby for shopping.

We stayed for a week in July 2024. A fantastic apartment in a perfect location. With a terrace, views of the estuary, and very well-equipped. It's about a 5-10 minute walk from the beach (a large inlet), surrounded by good restaurants, and easy parking (at least in July). Paulo gave us some great recommendations for places to visit, bars, and restaurants. It's wonderful to walk along the beach or its walkways. It's also not usually that stifling heat we've been suffering from in the Iberian Peninsula these past summers. It's 15 minutes from Aveiro. I also recommend visiting the chapel, museum, and shop at Vista Alegre. A place to come back again. However, I recommend always staying on Costa Nova beach. We found Barra beach to be overcrowded.

We went to the ‚Äúone ATM‚Äù in town to get cash because the restaurant we had already eaten at informed us when we tried to pay that they only took cash. This ATM didn‚Äôt have any cash, apparently. Great location. The staff is friendly and helpful. Decent size room. The AC didn‚Äôt work, thankfully, I was able to open the window. Unfortunately they put me in a room without the ocean view. Pretty clean space. The breakfast was pretty good.

Amazing stay in an amazing locale. The hotel looks unassuming from the outside, but it's modern and gorgeous inside! The room was well thought out from the desk to the sitting bench to the closets to the huge bathroom with plenty of towels and towel hooks. The staff were also incredibly kind. Everyone interacted with there was friendly and went out of their way to help me. They were fantastic English speakers. I'm already dreaming about my next trip! I wouldn't stay anywhere else in the area

I am making the review covering it by parts: 1. Accessibility, place, the local area.
1.Acessibilty- Easy access by car through highways "A25" and "EN's" (nationals), no fuss, parking wise you can find lots of public spaces on roads nearby.
2. Cozy room(3rd floor), safe locker, mini bar, lots of space, we requested a baby bed and the space was suitable for it. Bed  mattress queen size, WC with bathtub, hairdryer, and make up mirror.
3. We went in January to this place, so low season regarding occupancy and we notice that at night some restaurants and bars were open and with some medium attendance so expect high season to be quite crowdy.
Extra note: the view to the lighthouse and seaside was amazing.

My family and me stayed here for 2 nights. The location is perfect, in front of the Farol square with a breathtaking view overlooking the sea. We had two rooms categories, one was a refurbished suite on the 3rd floor, the other wasn't and lacked modernization and air conditioning. Breakfast was great, wifi had good consistent signal everywhere in the hotel. Staff was polite but not very helpful in providing touristic information. The beach is just a few steps away.

The location, the views, the room size and the great breakfast make up for all the small details that it's lacking (like good door locks). It's very clean. Pay the extra 10‚Ç¨ to get the superior room. You will get a nice balcony and a lot of space!

Don‚Äôt go there. The maracuja caipirinha tasted like rum mixed with water, we asked to change it 3 times and they just added more sugar. We didn‚Äôt want to pay for it and didn‚Äôt drink it but the bar manager insisted that we had to pay. Never had such a bad cocktail in my whole life and very unfriendly staff.

We had good experience with the food. And ask for americano or a large coffee if you wanna get a regular coffee, otherwise you get a strong but small portion (as everywhere in that area). You can have more sorts of coffee with milk, cream etc. From snacks we had sandwiches and burgers, all was tasty. Not much English despite they are located at the hotel.

Don't eat the pastries. The natas were burnt and a day old. Croissants also tasted stale.
Asked for different croissants and got the same burnt natas back.  Sometimes you just can't win. Maybe lunch is better.
Gorgeous place! Very nice staff. Absolute beautiful design. Paella is highly recommended! There are 3 types. We really felt at home here.

This location has great drinks! Must try the caipirinhas. They also serve food well past regular dinner hours which is perfect for late night snacks. The only downside is that service can be slow and inattentive at times.

A beautiful small hotel (villa with 3 floors and several rooms) located on the "beach promondory" of the Costa Nova" near Aveiro. You need to choose a room (at a higher price) with a sea view (this means an inner bay, not the open ocean) - these rooms are larger with a big balcony and the view is much nicer than the opposite rooms facing the street.  The rooms facing to the street are also very small. The ocean view also allows you to see flocks of flamingos with binoculars or a cell phone etc. The surroundings are very nice, cute typical Portuguese colorful striped houses, long promenade along them and along the sea. Right next to the hoel is an excellent fish restaurant, fruit/vegetable shop and market with fish, other goodies, cheese, wine, olives pastries and of course a fish restaurant upstairs, pharmacy and big parking place. The beach - open ocean - is a few minutes walk away. The beaches are gorgeous - long stretches of wild, sandy, but manicured beaches, with restaurants where you can watch amazing sunsets while having a carafe of sangria. By car it's a few minutes to the centre of Aveiro and the university, but there is a bus service too. Breakfast is possible in the detached building of the hotel, where there is also a reception with 24 h-service (about 50 m from the hotel villa). The cleaning is precise. Overall, I definitely recommend the hotel - we spent a little over a week here as part of a business trip (scientific conference at the university) and a shorter holiday.

review_text:
This company was very prompt in the beginning to inspect the problem and diagnose it.  They needed a part and asked for a 50% deposit for the job.  I agreed and they said it would be 2-3 weeks for the part to arrive.  I texted the technician after about a month and he said the part had not arrived. After 2 months later I tried to call the technician and no answer.  I then tried to contact the company and no response.  I finally got them to answer a text and they asked who had worked on the job.  Now another month has passed and I haven't been able to get anyone to answer my texts or calls.  I don't know what happened but they seem to have just quit doing business or something and I am out the deposit.

After the response to my original review, the only contact I have been able to get from them is to refute my review here.  I have sent multiple emails and texts to them but no response.  I am sure this was an honest mistake but they are not even trying to help me rectify it.  Just ignoring it is not good business.

Continuation of my review.  I finally after 3 months of calling, texting, and email got some to actually meet with me today.  It is kind of a raquete.  In most cases when everything goes well they probably do good work, but in case I think I finally understand what they are doing here.  It appears to be a message board for handymen to find jobs.  If they finish the job, everything is great.  In my case, it appears the man doing the job left town, probaby back in July, and now the owner and his salesman, I guess, just say not our problem, our names are not on any of your documents.  The only record that I am sure they have is my initial contact on their website, but like other website messengers I have used it did not send me a copy of my initial email.  So, I have learned, and if I could give them less than 1 star I would.  So, beware maybe other sites are better but I would stay far away from this one, and I still can't find their office in Aveiro.  It looks to me like it doesn't exist.

Me and my (Italian) wife saw this restaurant on the page of an influencer and decided to give it a try, also to see if it's really as Italian as they say it is. The restaurant is really well located, and you would think that because of the central location it would be overpriced, but it turned out to be not true. The staff was very professional and friendly, providing excellent service. Now to what matters the most, the food. I ordered the Pasta alla Forma and my wife had the Gnocchi ai 4 Formaggi. The gnocchi were really tasty, soft and the cheese tasted really good. We shared the dish and were left satisfied. The original station was opened in 1864 with the inauguration of the Linha do Norte (North Line). In 1916, the building underwent a major renovation, during which 59 azulejo panels were added to the fa√ßade. The tiles were designed by Lic√≠nio Pinto and Francisco Pereira and produced by the F√°brica da Fonte Nova. The tile panels follow a dual theme: those on the platform side introduce travel destinations, while those facing the city depict scenes of everyday life in Aveiro. Due to growing rail demand in the late 20th century, a new contemporary station building was added, while the old station has been preserved for its cultural and historical significance. Today, the station is served by Alfa Pendular, Intercidades, Regionais, and Porto Urban Trains, making it a key hub in Portugal‚Äôs rail network.

review_text:
The address was a little tricky to find at first, as Google Maps directed us the wrong way, we eventually located it with the help of a nearby shop. Once found, access was easy with the self check-in and door code system.
Be prepared for a couple of flights of stairs, and a motion light would have been useful for our early departure. The communal areas were spotless, and the kitchen was exceptionally well equipped, even better than many Airbnbs I‚Äôve stayed in, with everything you‚Äôd need to prepare meals, including a coffee machine.
The bedroom was super clean, comfortable, and thoughtfully laid out. The en-suite bathroom could benefit from a towel rail for drying towels, but otherwise it was great.
The location was a pleasant surprise, the train station is just a three-minute walk away, and there‚Äôs also an underground passage that takes you straight to the bus terminal across the road. That was a big win for us, as one of our group had an early bus to catch (just note that the escalators aren‚Äôt running early in the morning).
Overall, a great stay, clean, convenient, and well set up for short visits.

Check in was scheduled to happen at 15h, got a call to ask if it was possible to check in later at 17h. I agreed and when I got there, the number was offline, the manager had to come greet us in (which was lucky since he was about to leave).

The walls are paper thin, the bathroom floor was flooded after every shower despite our best efforts and the closet nearly fell on me since it's not secure to the wall - as soon as I reached for the handle it started tipping over. A 2.5meter closet. Suffice to say we didn't really store our clothes during our already shortened stay.

Perhaps we got the worse room or got unlucky, but from my experience, it's unlikely for me to return here.

Note: We rented this with a 40% discount and we took the price into consideration when grading Aveiro White House.

Location: right next to the station, but a few minutes walk (15mins)  from the center and the tourist area.

Accomodations: we rented an apartment, it was nice and pretty clean, had everything we needed (basic things, no luxuries)

Surroundings: supermarket is a few minutes down the road, its small but it has most things. Pharmacy also down the road. Train station and bus stops right next door.

review_text: This monument honors Dr. Louren√ßo Sim√µes Peixinho, a visionary leader who played a key role in the modernization of Aveiro. It was erected in 1952 by the city at the starting point of the central avenue that now bears his name. Dr. Peixinho served as the president of the Aveiro Municipal Council (a role equivalent to today‚Äôs mayor) from 1918 to 1942. During his 24-year tenure, he spearheaded major urban development projects, including the creation of the main avenue, public parks, and hospitals‚Äîlaying the foundation for the city‚Äôs transformation in the 20th century.

Declined the starter meats and bread which is offered to diners and went straight for the main course from the wide ranging choice of meals in the menu - half a grilled chicken served with boiled rice and chips and a green salad (had to check whether it was served with any side dishes because the menu wasn't clear). My recent birthday celebration at Churrasqueira Sal na Brasa was an absolute success, largely thanks to their excellent service and delicious food. I booked in advance for a large group, and upon arrival, our table was perfectly prepared, and the staff even offered to store our birthday cake until later ‚Äì a thoughtful touch that set a positive tone for the evening.
We started with some appetizers before diving into the main courses. My girlfriend and I shared two dishes: the Picanha (top sirloin cap) and Bifes de Peru (turkey steaks). The meat was exceptional, especially the Picanha, which was cooked to perfection and incredibly flavorful. The entire table was impressed with their meals, and everyone had more than enough side dishes to feel completely satisfied.
While we brought our own birthday cake, the staff was still incredibly accommodating, providing everything we needed to enjoy it comfortably. The service throughout the evening was consistently friendly and attentive, making us feel well-cared for.
The restaurant itself had warm lighting and a comfortable ambiance, contributing to a relaxed and enjoyable dining experience.
Churrasqueira Sal na Brasa delivered on all fronts for a memorable birthday dinner.

Sadly, we had not been reading the Google reviews beforehand, as we now see that several others has had similar experiences. We tried to call the two telephone numbers provided by Urban suites, but no answer. Refusing to sleep in the room, we went out and checked in at another hotel in the middle of the night (Hotel Aveiro center‚ù§). When we texted Urban suites in the morning and they actually answered us, they started denying any bedbugs (saying they checked the room and didn't see any bugs), they denied that we had called (although we obviously have proof of that). We asked for a refund, but of course they rejected us and implied that we were making everything up and lying. So in short, nasty rooms and unpleasant staff. The location is acceptable I guess. Would not recommend.

Disappointing Experience at Domino's Pizza in Aveiro

I recently visited Domino's Pizza in Aveiro with a group of friends, excited to try the "all you can eat" menu that included unlimited drinks. Unfortunately, the experience fell short of our expectations, and I would like to share my negative review with you.

Upon arrival, we were informed that the "all you can eat" menu did not include unlimited drinks as we had anticipated. Instead, we were offered a menu without any drinks included, but at the same price. This discrepancy from the advertised offer left us disappointed, as we had specifically chosen the restaurant for the option of unlimited drinks.

Furthermore, we expressed our dissatisfaction to the staff and the misunderstanding that had occurred. We were disappointed that no discount or remedy was offered for the inconvenience. It would have been appreciated if a gesture of goodwill had been made to compensate for the discomfort caused.

Regarding the food, we were let down by the quality that didn't resemble a real pizza in the slightest. The pizzas lacked flavor, the texture of the crust was not authentic, and it seemed that the ingredients used were of low quality. We didn't expect to have an artisanal pizza, but the difference was so noticeable that it was difficult to truly enjoy the food.

In conclusion, my experience at Domino's Pizza in Aveiro was disappointing due to the lack of unlimited drinks as promised in the "all you can eat" menu, the absence of any remedy or discount offered for the inconvenience, and the quality of the food that bore no resemblance to a real pizza. I cannot fully recommend this restaurant to those seeking a satisfying pizza experience.

I hope that my review can be helpful to those looking for alternatives for a pizza evening in Aveiro.

Every dish was outstanding: extremely tasteful, beautifully presented, and with generous portions. We chose the CARPACCIO DI MANZO RAFFAELLO as a starter and had for main; LINGUINE AL PESTO CON STRACCIATELLA and TORTELLONI DI PERA E GORGONZOLA. We finished with CHEESECAKE AL PISTACCHIO.
Il Libertino is located slightly outside the city center of Aveiro, but it‚Äôs absolutely worth the short trip if you appreciate authentic and beautifully crafted Italian cuisine. A true gem, definitely to be repeated!

I really wanted to like this place, it‚Äôs so pretty but although it has good flavor the pasta was overcooked . The gnocchi literally melted in your mouth and turned to mush. My tuna was cooked to within an inch of its life, super dry and chewy. Disappointed and high prices.

Unfortunately, after our visit to the restaurant, we both ended up with stomach upset. Mine was quite severe and ended with vomiting. Either the tortellini or the cheesecake was not fresh. The place itself is charming, and the dishes were tasty, but the suffering afterwards ruined the overall experience.

The food was good, but not worth waiting ao long - we waited almost 1 hour for it. also, they said we couldn‚Äôt get entrees before the main dish. It makes you wonder what‚Äôs the point of offering entrees. I don‚Äôt quite recommend

Il Libertino in Aveiro is a charming Italian restaurant that offers a delightful dining experience. The cozy atmosphere, with its low lighting and tasteful decor, creates a romantic and intimate setting.

The service was impeccable. Our server was attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable about the menu. They were always on hand to ensure that our needs were met throughout the evening.

The food was truly exceptional. We started with a delicious plate of bruschetta, followed by a creamy risotto di zucca and a classic spaghetti alla carbonara. Both dishes were cooked to perfection, with the flavors blending harmoniously. To finish, we indulged in a decadent profiterole, which was the perfect sweet ending to our meal.

While there was a minor oversight with our dessert order, the staff quickly rectified the situation with apologies, demonstrating their commitment to customer satisfaction.

Overall, Il Libertino is a fantastic choice for a romantic dinner or a night out with friends. The combination of delicious food, attentive service, and a cozy atmosphere makes it a memorable experience.

review_text:
For a fresh seafood lunch, I decided to try a Mexican restaurant that offered this option. The place is very well-maintained, with a great themed atmosphere.

The staff was incredibly quick, friendly, and smiling‚Äîthey were all excellent. If I lived in Aveiro, I would definitely return.

There was just one downside, which is why I wouldn't order this taco again next time‚Äîthe octopus was overly masked by the other ingredients. However, this doesn't change my overall assessment of the place, which I think is excellent. I would probably really enjoy the original tacos.

Our waiter was very attentive, always very polite, and regularly informed us when our food would be ready. We didn't know the chef, but the food was phenomenal! Very hot, you could tell it had just been made. The sauces, both for the naan and the chicken, were very tasty, and the restaurant was clean and organized! The bathrooms were also in very good condition. Overall, the food, the service, and the establishment were great! I highly recommend going to this restaurant. The staff was friendly and attentive, and the cozy atmosphere made it even better. Rang Mahal is the perfect spot if you‚Äôre looking to enjoy both authentic Indian food and delicious Italian classics under one roof. Highly recommended!üòçüòçüòç

review_text: Would definitely recommend this place to have a cheap meal. Lunch menu includes soup, main dish(meat or fish) and coffee, it costs 7.50‚Ç¨ if one chooses meat option and 8‚Ç¨ if it's fish. There is a good variety of options and they're all simple and traditional. As drinks are not included in the price, a finish price will be around 10‚Ç¨. Service was fine, the lady who served us was quite friendly. The main downside is how this restaurant is arranged, because it really looks and feels like a cheap ordinary cafe and the bathroom definitely needs renovation.

place_name: Onda Verde Restaurante - Prato do dia
review_text: This is a treasure for budget travelers in the over-touristy town of Aveiro! The restaurant was full of locals during the lunch time. The "menu do dia" includes soup, main dish and a coffee. It costs 7.5‚Ç¨ if you prefer meat, and 8‚Ç¨ for fish. The bread is not included, neither are the drinks and desert. Vinho da casa costs 3‚Ç¨ for half a liter. They offer simple Portuguese dishes which are tasty and big. On the pictures: Vegetable soup, Robalo with vegetables, Prego no prato (beef).

review_text: Good, cheap, simple food. Stewed vitella with spaghetti was amazing. Service is typical of family restaurants so don't come if it's packed and you want a quick bite

We were visiting Aveiro with friends and booked the restaurant for lunch. We reached little early but were accommodated. Not only this we were provided with a good location table. The staff is very helpful and friendly. For comfort of our friends they spoke English. The service was excellent and food was served hot. We had ordered two pizza, a pasta and a salad. Food is tasty and garlic bread was super delicious. Reasonably priced.

We had a delicious lunch there, with wine, passion fruit sangria and great steaks. They made a special steak for us with hot pepper to please some guests. I had the Chef steak which was perfect, tender and juicy as a good steak should be.
The sides were also very good, specially the french fries, which were perfectly crispy on the outside.
For dessert we had the homemade chocolate mousse and also the zabaione cream. They were both rich and nice, but the later was so delicate and tasty, that was simply delicious!
We look forward coming back there to try the rest of the menu!

The rooms were very basic, and the windows only tilted open, which was unpleasant in the summer heat. The showers were particularly unhygienic: the water didn't drain, they were dirty, and they smelled bad. Aside from that, the rest of the accommodation was clean. Unfortunately, some of the other guests didn't always respect the quiet hours, which was a bit bothersome.

We found it unusual that we were supposed to leave our room keys in a basket at the reception whenever we left the building. After a short discussion where we pointed out the security risk‚Äîthat someone could simply grab a random key and enter a stranger‚Äôs room‚Äîwe were allowed to keep our key.

The breakfast was tasty and there was a good variety.

The price of ‚Ç¨39 for two people was very cheap. For this price, you can't expect luxury, but the accommodation was perfectly fine for one night.

Fusion Cowork in Aveiro is a fantastic coworking space that provides an excellent environment for people to work collaboratively and efficiently. As someone who has worked there through my company, I can attest to the professionalism and friendliness of the staff and other professionals in the space.

The coworking space is spacious, well-lit, and thoughtfully designed, which creates a comfortable and inspiring atmosphere. The high-speed internet connection is reliable, ensuring that I can work seamlessly without any interruptions. Additionally, the meeting rooms are well-equipped with all the necessary amenities, which are perfect for meetings, brainstorming sessions, and presentations.

The best part about Fusion Cowork is the community of professionals who work there. They are a friendly and diverse group of individuals who are always willing to collaborate, share ideas and network. The social events organized by the space also provide a great opportunity to meet new people and create lasting connections.

Overall, I would highly recommend Fusion Cowork to anyone looking for a professional and welcoming coworking space in Aveiro. It is an excellent place to work, network, and grow your business.

The interview impressed me and I reached out to Rafael and he setup an initial Zoom Call and explained the entire Mortgage Process to me, for US expats moving to Portugal and planning to buy property.

We finally closed the Public Deed on time and I travelled to Madeira for the Deed and we got the Keys to the property in Feb 2024.

Rafael and his team (Frederico Franca) provided exceptional service and made the process totally smooth. They reached out to my builder to get all the documents needed for the Deed and liaised with the NovoBanco Bank Manager on my behalf to make sure everything gets done on time and there are no hiccups during the Public Deed Closing.

If you are planning to buy property in Portugal, please go with Rafael and his team for your Mortgage Needs. They are the most professional and the best team out there helping US and EU expats buy property in Portugal and get a Mortgage.

I give them 10/10 for their professional, communication, ethical and a very knowledgeable team. Highly recommended. Thanks Rafael and Fred for making the Home buying and Mortgage FInancing  process extremely smooth for me.

Their communication was excellent throughout, keeping us informed at every step. Their genuine care and willingness to go above and beyond truly set them apart.

Thanks to Rafael and his team, we successfully purchased our dream home in a beautiful location, and we couldn‚Äôt be more grateful. Their advice and support made all the difference, and we will forever be thankful for their hard work and dedication. Our kids will grow up appreciating the wonderful environment and, most importantly, the warmth of a true family home. Thank you all from the bottom of our hearts.

If you‚Äôre considering buying property in Portugal, especially if you‚Äôre navigating a complex process like obtaining a mortgage or dealing with legal matters, we wholeheartedly recommend Rafael, Fred, and Emilia. They‚Äôre the team you can trust to make your dreams a reality!

The team assembled by Rafael was consciously aware of providing us with the best care, attention, and options needed to buy a new home. This cultural venue beautifully balances contemporary art exhibitions with panoramic views of the canal, appearing to float above the water on arch-supported columns. Originally built in the early 15th century as a tidal-powered watermill, the structure was developed atop the canal arches known as Casa dos Arcos. Over the 19th and 20th centuries, it served various purposes‚Äîfirst as a warehouse for coal and citrus, then as a printing house for a local newspaper, and even housed Aveiro's first steam engine. In 1903, it became home to the School of Industrial Design. From 1919, it functioned as the office of a maritime company, and from 1925 to 1993, it served as the official building for the Port Authority of Aveiro (Capitania). Following a remodeling in 2003, the ground floor was transformed into a public art gallery, while the upper floor now hosts meeting rooms for the Aveiro City Council.

Bordalo II's R√£ is one of the most iconic works by Portuguese artist Bordalo II, known for his urban installations made from discarded materials and recycled waste. This enormous, colorful frog is part of the "Big Trash Animals" series, with which the artist denounces human impact on the environment and the destruction of biodiversity.

Reflective Art
The work, visible in several Portuguese cities, is constructed entirely from discarded plastic, metal, rubber, and everyday objects, transformed into a gigantic, surprisingly lifelike and powerful animal. The R√£ (frog), in addition to its strong visual impact, sends a clear message: nature suffers under the weight of our waste.

Why see it?
- It's an extraordinary example of sustainable street art.
- It's striking for its creativity, technique, and social significance.
- Perfect for lovers of urban photography and engaged art.
- It symbolizes the new face of Portuguese contemporary art.

In short: Bordalo II's R√£ is not just an urban sculpture, but a powerful visual statement and a form of artistic activism that leaves its mark.

Disappointing Experience at Binho

I rarely leave negative reviews, but my experience at Binho was disappointing enough that I feel compelled to share.

I ordered what was one of the more expensive bottles on the menu, expecting a quality pour. Unfortunately, the wine was clearly off ‚Äî either poorly stored or past its prime. I politely brought this to the staff‚Äôs attention, hoping for a reasonable resolution.

What made the situation worse wasn‚Äôt just the wine itself, but how the owner handled it. Rather than addressing the concern with professionalism or even basic courtesy, I was met with defensiveness and a dismissive attitude. There was no genuine attempt to listen or make it right ‚Äî something I‚Äôd expect from any establishment, especially one that positions itself as a WINE BAR.

Everyone makes mistakes, and sometimes bottles do go bad ‚Äî that‚Äôs understandable. But how a business chooses to handle those moments speaks volumes about its values and service standards. Sadly, in this case, the response left a sour taste that went far beyond the wine.

I hope Binho takes this as an opportunity to improve how they handle customer concerns in the future.

A Taste of Tradition: Generous Portions and Authentic Flavors in a Portuguese Setting

In my quest to explore the rich culinary traditions of Portugal, I found myself at this charming restaurant, where the essence of traditional Portuguese cuisine takes center stage. The experience was a testament to the country‚Äôs reputation for generous portions, bold flavors, and heartfelt hospitality.

My meal began with a classic Portuguese soup, a warm and comforting dish that exemplified simplicity done right. The ingredients were fresh, and the flavors were well-balanced, providing a perfect introduction to what lay ahead.

For the main course, I chose the grilled cod‚Äîa dish synonymous with Portuguese gastronomy. The portion was impressively generous, reflecting the restaurant's commitment to hospitality. The cod was expertly prepared, with a beautifully charred exterior that locked in its natural flavors while remaining moist and flaky inside. Paired with traditional accompaniments, this dish truly showcased the depth of Portugal‚Äôs culinary heritage.

The portions, as mentioned, were substantial, ensuring that no guest leaves unsatisfied. This, combined with the attention to flavor and preparation, elevates the restaurant to a must-visit status for those seeking an authentic Portuguese dining experience.

Beyond the food, the atmosphere of the restaurant deserves recognition. The rustic d√©cor and warm ambiance provide an inviting setting that enhances the meal, making it more than just a dining experience‚Äîit feels like a journey into Portugal‚Äôs cultural heart.

In summary, this restaurant delivers on all fronts: generous servings, expertly prepared dishes, and an ambiance that reflects the soul of Portugal. Whether you‚Äôre a local or a traveler, it‚Äôs a place that guarantees satisfaction and a genuine taste of tradition.

A BIG DECEPTION
Everything is very well thought out, the photographs, the information provided, etc. You don't realize what's going on until you get far enough away. And that's when you realize what they're really offering you is a shared apartment, full of lies.
Because it doesn't have a pool, a hair salon, or reception until 8 p.m., the rooms are very noisy, there's a lack of security, flimsy doors and locks, and no public parking.
In our experience, we were quite lucky with the people we shared with, a very nice couple from Madrid in the same situation as us.
As for the location and decor, they were very good, but the shower in the RV I rented two years ago was larger. Two of the three bedrooms were quite small and poorly ventilated, with no air conditioning, although it was necessary. The beds were very comfortable, but not enough to make up for all the negatives.
Honestly, I don't recommend it at all; there are better and much cheaper places.
All of this was brought to Booking.com's attention, and the most they got was a small financial compensation.

Ficamos num piso s√≥ para n√≥s, pois os outros quartos n√£o foram alugados. O atendimento foi muito simp√°tico, mas foi-nos dito que deste andar vai sofrer obras grandes e ficar bastante melhor. Desejo boa sorte parte o futuro.

Sometimes you only discover a place after you leave. Casa do Caf√© located in the main square, many restaurants near by, tables are spread in the public area. We had a brunch and wanted to have a memory from this wonderful day. An aroma and flavor that could bring memories. This coffee reminds us that great day with every sip we take. ‚òï
We had a bad experience because we bought a coffee machine that it was broken and the seller didn‚Äôt wanted to change it or money back.
We picked up several different roasts while on vacation, and they have all been very good. I wish I could order some to be delivered here in Western Canada!

We were told by a waitress that they did not have any table left, yet 2 were freed up 10 seconds later and another waiter sat us down. They were out of all soft drinks and did not agree to serve tap water. Bacalhau √† Br√°s was exceedingly salty, making it barely edible. The other dishes were not great either unfortunately.

At 4pm we wanted a drink and try some cod.
There were only 2 tables occupied. We waited 30 minutes before a lazy waiter went to our table. He was yawing at our table with his mouth wide open.
Nothing i wanted to order was available anymore.
So we decided to just have a drink, one beer and one gin and tonic. Before we had our drinks, we had to wait doe another 15 minutes...
Just stay away from this place.

Just lovely and yummy. We popped in the other day with the four of us for dinner. I was starving and ordered a starter with bacalhau croquettes. They were simple and just perfect. We all a main dish, either a combination of flakes and potato and eggs and just yummy stuff, or the vegetarian dish with goat's cheese, or a chunk of bacalhau with perfect potatoes, onion, garlic and lovely taste. We all finished every last bit of it. I don't understand the negative comments here. This is a great place, good kitchen, excellent service... and I'd recommend to everyone!

Little gem. If you're trying to avoid tourist traps and overpriced cantina food: that's definitely the best spot in Aveiro. The entire menu is based on codfish, and if you like it, you won't be disappointed. The food is really fresh and tasty- I had the tasting platter (13‚Ç¨) so i could get a bit of every dish, and everything was delicious (really loved the cod, egg and chickpea salad though). Most of the other items on the menu are between 6 and 9 euros.  The staff was really kind and the service was fast. Would definitely recommend!

The service was sooooooo slow!!  They only had two waitresses for all the tables... we waited more than an hour to get our food.   I don't recommend this place at all!

review_text:
Taking a moliceiro tour is definitely one of the must-do experiences in Aveiro.

Gliding through the canals on those colorful boats is fun and gives you a nice feel for the city‚Äôs charm.

I‚Äôm only docking one star because our guide seemed a bit inexperienced ‚Äî we got the basic history about Aveiro‚Äôs salt trade and its famous sweet ovos moles, but not much beyond that.

Maybe the guide was just new, or maybe Aveiro itself doesn‚Äôt have much to talk about ‚Äî hard to tell!

That said, at around ‚Ç¨15 per person, it‚Äôs still absolutely worth doing.

If you can, request an older or more seasoned guide for a richer experience.

I only had one day in Aveiro, and while it‚Äôs often called the ‚ÄúVenice of Portugal,‚Äù I personally found it a bit quiet compared to other Portuguese cities.

Still, the canals and moliceiros are unique and make for great photos.

place_name: Restaurante Palhu√ßa ‚Äì Gastronomia Portuguesa em Aveiro
review_text:
Palhuca Restaurant in Aveiro offers a delightful culinary experience with a menu that showcases the rich flavors of the region. The food was exceptional, with each dish beautifully prepared and full of authentic Portuguese taste. The restaurant was bustling with locals, which added a vibrant and welcoming atmosphere, hinting at its popularity among those who know good food in the area.

However, our experience was marred by an unexpected issue with the bill. We were surprised to find a 20% tip automatically added to our bill, written only in Portuguese. This charge was not communicated to us beforehand, and it left us feeling somewhat taken advantage of. It gave the impression that this practice might not be applied to locals, raising questions about fairness and transparency. While we enjoyed the meal, this incident dampened our overall experience, and we left feeling a bit used. We hope the restaurant can address this issue to ensure a more transparent and inclusive experience for all patrons.

We would left 20% tip easily for the climate and great food‚Ä¶

Confeitaria Ramos is one of Aveiro‚Äôs most iconic and beloved pastry shops, steeped in history and tradition. Established generations ago, this family-run establishment has managed to preserve its original charm and authenticity over the years. Located in the heart of Aveiro, it is well-known for offering some of the finest traditional Portuguese pastries, making it a must-visit for anyone exploring the city.

What sets Confeitaria Ramos apart is its dedication to preserving recipes that have been passed down through the family. Their range of pastries includes Aveiro‚Äôs local specialties, with the famous "ovos moles" being a highlight. These delicate sweets, made from egg yolks and sugar, are wrapped in thin wafers and are a staple of the region. The quality of ingredients and the care put into every pastry is evident, resulting in a delightful and authentic culinary experience.

The shop itself exudes a warm and inviting atmosphere, with friendly staff who are always eager to share the history behind their creations. Whether you‚Äôre enjoying a quick coffee with a pastel de nata or savoring their regional specialties, Confeitaria Ramos offers a taste of Aveiro's rich confectionery heritage that has stood the test of time.
